{
  "name": "Locus: Mangler's Mask",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>(Requires attunement by a creature with the Extra Attack feature. The properties of this item are affixed to a wonderous item.)</em></p><p><em>This item is a @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3]{locus} and can be combined with other <strong>Loci </strong>per the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.rules.JournalEntry.nniVtdJB1oyk5Sa3.JournalEntryPage.zI0VWGKnYZqz6sKd]{Combining Loci} rules.</em></p><p>An eerie carved <strong>Oni</strong> mask that is a swirl of golden and red color. Adorned with sharp horns and even sharper sets of fangs, 6 of which protrude out from the grinning mouth. This was found in Er'ist'ra'tar's lair.</p><p>While attuned the mask magically marks a <strong>wonderous item</strong> of your choice. This can be done during a short or long rest, requires 10 minutes to complete and it upon completion leaves a visible impression of the oni's mask and especially the fanged grin.</p><p><strong>Effect: </strong>Divide your maximum hit points into fourths and these will be use to identify the \"bracket\" you fall into. At the top and bottom bracket you are empowered by <em>Mangler's Might </em>which drives you to leave a trail of torn and broken bodies in your wake.</p><ul><li>25% or below = Increase your attack rolls by 2d4 and you add your proficiency bonus to all your damage rolls, and you expand your critical range by 2.</li><li>26% through 74% = No benefit</li><li>75% or above = Increase your attack rolls by 1d4, you add your proficiency bonus to all your damage rolls and you expand your critical range by 1.</li></ul><p><strong>Special:</strong> When you are reduced to 0 hit points, not stable and unconscious <strong>@UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.actors.Actor.arMRLJ1uoCV209eJ]{The Mangler}</strong> manifests itself at the closest unoccupied space within 10 feet of your body.</p><p>When it takes damage or is more than 30 feet away from your body, it disappears until the start of your next turn (manifesting itself at the closest unoccupied space within 10 feet of you). It will only go away when you are dead, stabilized, or above 0 hit points. While The Mangler is active, it attacks the closest target to your body within 30 feet, rolling at random for targets if there are multiple. If The Mangler reduces a creature to 0 hit points then your next death saving throw is made at advantage and a roll of 15 or higher is treated like a natural 20; healing you an amount equal to your character level.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
